<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
At Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Merrill Lynch, Research Analysts are aligned by both product (debt or equity) and industry group (healthcare, technology, energy, etc.). Working alongside some of the most talented professionals in the industry, Research Analysts gain the sector-specific expertise critical to building a career in research, and contribute significantly to the in-depth research we distribute to clients worldwide.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
	
<p class="bac">
Associate Interns participate in a 10 week program based in Asia providing a unique opportunity and exposure to life in research.  In addition to learning opportunities there are formal and social opportunities to interact and network with senior colleagues.
</p>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Placement</H3>
<p class="bac">
Associate Interns are placed directly with a specific team throughout the internship.  Group placement is determined by considering business needs and the interests/skills of the intern.  The groups span across country and industry, these include but not limited to (not all groups exist in all countries):
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Country
		<ul class="bac">
			<li>Hong Kong</li>
			<li>Japan</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

<br>
<H3 class="bac">Responsibilities</H3>
<p class="bac">
Research Associate Interns will work closely with the team and some of the tasks include modeling/analysis, conducting primary research, attend internal/external client meetings. Some responsibilities are conducted regularly (daily, weekly, etc.) while others are longer-term, ad hoc projects over the internship period.
</p>

